title: Salty and Tall Race for the March of Dimes
University of Oklahoma Cycling's Land Ronde
description: Races are Saturday and Sunday. RR, TTT, and Crit.
course:
RR- Rolling course around Lake Stanley Draper. 14.8 mile Circuit through blistering winds. 
TTT- 12 miles out and back section of the RR course
Crit- East of Lloyd Noble Center across Jenkins Ave on OU Campus in Research Park. Near Stevensen Research Center.
registration: Online registration will be available at www.usacycling.org  for $10/event. A late fee of $5 will be added to on-site registration.
notes: The Land Ronde is a collegiate Race Event in the SCCCC. Security/Police and  EMT and voluteer support will be present. Food/drinks may be provided depending sponsor participation.
directions:
RR/TTT--From I-240, exit at Sooner Rd. and continue south to SW 104th St. Turn Left on SW 104th
St. and continue to Lake Stanley Draper Marina.--OR-- take 12th Ave from Norman, North to 104th and turn Right. 

Crit-- Stevenson Research Center on Jenkins Ave near HW-9, across Jenkins Ave from Llyod Noble Center.

title: Tribbey Cinco de Mayo Omnium
description: Combining this year the historic Tribbey Time Trial with a Road Race to follow in the afternoon, should provide riders the early season challenge they have been waiting all winter for.
course: The TT course is as it has always been, hilly and demanding. The new Road Race encompasses portions of the infamous 89er Stage Race and is guaranteed to provide the riders with the feel of that race with a shorter but still demanding course. Larry Smith of the Bicycle Shoppe will once again be offering an incentive of 2000.00 plus dollars for the lowest time under an hour for the time trial. The hour has never been broken on the demanding TT course.
registration: Registration: All riders riding both the TT and RR are required to pre-register online @ USACycling.org by Thursday, May 3, 2012. Any person wanting to register the day of will pay an additional $10.00 for doing so. Riders can ride both the RR and TT or TT individually. There is no requirement to ride both, but you must ride the TT to inter the RR. Entry fee for the Omnium event is $40.00 which is non refundable.   Should you elect to ride the TT only the entry fee will be 20.00. Day of/on site entry fee for TT is 25.00. Registration will open @ 8:00am and the 1st rider off will start @ 9:00am. Rider start will be in order of online registration followed by day of registration. A portion of the entry fee will go to USAC for insurance and online registration and BRAOK support. One day licenses will be available on site.
notes: The race will be scored on points with points from the TT added to points earned in the RR. Overall highest points winners will be eligible for the prize list. This is an open event with no regard to gender or age in the road race or overall scoring. Riders may ride in the categories they are eligible to ride in. There will be neutral mechanical support and a rolling enclosure with lead sheriff and moto support. Medical support will be on call.
directions: From OKC East I-40 exit I-40, south on hwy102. Cross hwy 9 continue south to Tribbey. Approximately 10miles from hwy 9 and 20 miles from I-40.

address.street: ROMAN NOSE STATE PARK, HWY 8 A

title: St. Gregorys University Memorial Day Tour
St. Gregory's University Memorial Day Road Rac
description: The St. Gregory\'s University Memorial Day Road Race is a revival of one of the oldest road races in Oklahoma. It begins on the historic campus of St. Gregory\'s University and feaures a hill-top finish at the Sacred Heart Mission, the original home of the college.
course: The course follows rolling hills and smooth roads through rural Pottawatomie County from Shawnee to Konawa. The four mile approach to Sacred Heart is a challenging series of hills. If we have a strong headwind on race day expect an epic race day challenge!
registration:
For a better race day experience all racers are strongly encouraged to pre-register. There is no charge for on-line registration. There will be a $10 late registration charge for race-day on-site registration.
 register @ www.usacycling.org
notes: This is a point-to-point race with a spaghetti lunch and awards presentation for riders at the finish. Most racers and tour riders will ride a 35 mile return route back to the start but SAGs will be available for those not providing their own return transportation.
directions: The race begins on the St. Gregory\'s campus in Shawnee and ends at the Sacred Heart Mission in Konawa.

title: Oklahoma City Pro-Am Classic
description: The Oklahoma City Pro-Am Classic Criterium is a full day of high energy racing for both the amateur and elite cyclist.  Staged in the Business District in the heart OKC it offers an exciting atmosphere for the whole family.
course: A fast six corner .82 mile course with one screaming 90 degree turn.
registration: Registration opens February 8th at $35.  Registration increases to $40 on May 8th and day of is $45.
notes:
we will offer two races for the masters Men 40+: Two Men 40+ races will be offered this year: Master Men A and Master Men B. The Master Men A race is for Men 40+/50+/60+ Cat 1, 2 or 3. one race one prize list with 3 deep bonus for the top 50+ aand top 3 60+.  
The Master Men B race 40+/50+/60+ Cat 3, 4 or 5 same format as the A race. 

For more information contact OKCPAC@gmail.com

title: Tour de Trykes Twilght Criterium
description: twilight criterium in downtown Enid Oklahoma. Course is well lit.
course: Course has 8 turns with a fast downhill leading into a turn. Finish on a slight uphill.
registration: Online registration @ USACycling. Late registration 3.00 extra with day of registration 5.00 extra. A portion of the registration goes to USAC for insurance and to BROAK for state association fees.
directions: From the south on I35 take Hwy 412 into Enid, north on Independence to course. From the north I35 take 412 west into Enid, north on Independence to course. Plenty of of site parking.

title: Tour de Trykes
description: This is a road ride for bikes, trikes, recumbants, and tandems. Various course distances from 25 mi to 100 mi. Many course stops along the way with volunteers providing refreshments and care. This event is to rasie money for Amtrykes,(Theraputic tricycles for people with disabilities) and other Ambucs charitable projects.
course: The course is FLAT with various distances depending upon ability. There will be a 2-mile Family Fun Ride in addition to the tour.
registration: Single bike registartion is 22.00 befor August 15 and 27.00 after August 15. Tandems 40.00 before August 15 and 50.00 after August 15. T-shirts guaranteed to riders who register prior to August 15. Family fun ride registartion is 15.00 or 30.00 per family. (2 t-shirt limit)
directions: Downtown Enid Oklahoma @ DAvid Allen Memorial Ballpark, 301 S Grand Ave.

title: Blue Canyon Oklahoma Championship Time Trial
The Oklahoma State Category Road Race Championship
Bison Classic State Age-Group Road Championships
Family Fat Tire Festival 2
description:
2nd Annual Family Fat Tire Festival
Saturday November 3, 2012
10:00 a.m. 2:00 p.m.

Fun guided trail rides, mountain bike games, crafts, etc for the whole family.
course:
Beginner course -- approx 1.5 miles
Intermediate course -- approx 3.5 miles
Expert course -- approx 7 miles

All courses are offroad singletrack trails within Lake Thuderbird Clearbay trail system.  Beginner trail is suitable for very young riders -- graduated from training wheels.  Some adult assistance may be required to ride some infrequent obstacles.  Intermediate and Expert courses are progressively more difficult.
registration:
Reigstration -- free for all riders!
Pre-registration is encoruaged.  Pre-registered riders are entered into special doorprize drawing. Also those that pre-reg on line can complete (sign) the standard waiver electronically - that means no standing in line. Members with a license simply log into their USA Cycling account and non members can do the same by creating an account for no charge go to www.usacycling.org
directions:
Lake Thunderbird State Park -- Clearbay Entrance
Highway 9 -- 12 miles east of Interstate 35 in Norman, OK.

title: Rock The Mohawk Cx
description: The Oklahoma Grand Prix of Cyclocross Series is coming to Mohawk Park in Tulsa, Ok
course: Mostly flat and technical course with a few inclines and a short run-up
registration: Onsite registration opens at 9:00 am and closes 15 minutes prior to each race start time.  Look for the registration signs.
directions: Take the Mohawk Park entrance off E 36th St N then turn right on Cherokee Drive and follow the Pink Flamingos!
